Centane police arrested five men, aged 23, 24, 34, 28, 69 years old, and a 59-year-old woman with a huge quantity of dagga over the weekend."The suspects were arrested at Cebe, Nxaxo and Gaqa Villages on Saturday, at about 17:00," described police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha."They will appear before the Centane Magistrate's Court on Monday on charges of possession of dagga."He saidd that Centane police also closed a shebeen and confiscated huge amount of liquor on Saturday.Image: Some Centane police officers with the recovered dagga.